                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/511</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Caperton</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>By decrees of President issued today Senate has been dissolved and Chamber of
                    Deputies will be convoked as a Constituent Assembly to revise Constitution to
                    accord with treaty. This Constituent Assembly <pb facs="0397" n="321"
                        xml:id="pg_321"/> will act in accord with Executive Power. There is also
                    provided by decree a Council of State of twenty-one members appointed by
                    President to act with Government in drawing up and preparing such changes and
                    laws as may be necessary to be submitted to the Constituent Assembly and to
                    advise on such other matters as Government may desire.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. B. Caperton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
